Write a prolog program to implement insert_nth (I, N, L, R) that inserts an item I into Nth position
of list L to generate a list R.
Solution
insert_nth(I, 1, L, [I|L]):- !.
insert_nth(I, N, [H|T], [H|T1]):-
 N1 is N - 1,
 insert_nth(I, N1, T, T1).

Output 
| ?- insert_nth(4,0,[5,7,8,0],X).
no
| ?- insert_nth(4,1,[5,7,8,0],X).
X = [4,5,7,8,0]
yes
| ?- insert_nth(4,6,[5,7,8,0],X).
no
| ?-
